4.04/5  rDev -10%look: 3.75 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 3.5 |  overall: 4Pirate Bomb pours a watery, shiny dark brown with a bubbly, dark tan head--it's obvious it has thinned out.
When I was pouring this, I could smell the rum heat emanating off of the rim, then all of a sudden it was gone as I brought it to my nose, replaced by roasty coffee, caramel, nougat and wet cocoa.
Wow--sweet, round flavors of Tootsie Roll and fudge spoil the tongue, with caramel swirled coffee ice cream following right after. Actually, as I swirl it around my mouth, it almost tastes like a Butterfinger! There is some true gold spiced rum flavor without the heat, but there's not much coffee or Mexican spices to speak of. I can barely tell this was BOMB! A touch of wet cinnamon barely emerges as it warms, but there is more dry, aged dark oak barrel and walnut shell than cinnamon, and it's overall much sweeter than any of the other big name Prairie stouts I've had. 
The body is much thinner than regular BOMB!, and it's bubbly, with a slick stickiness. Overall it is less complex and less intense than Pirate Noir. 1,033 charactersSabtos, May 09, 2017
