4.26/5  rDev -5.1%look: 4.5 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.25A - A brown-black purely opaque body and a brown head that pours short and fades to a slim ring and a slight spotty cast.  You can see the viscosity in the way the beer forms waves in the pour.  Promises a real creamy treat.
S - Vanilla and alcohol warmth, a hint of chili, also a definite chocolate thread.
T - The chili note is front, not so much as spice but hinting at pepper flesh.  Not off-note, like green peppers, but more like jalapenos.  Underlying this, and coming forward in the middle and close is a strong chocolate hit, spiced hints of cinnamon.  The rum comes through with vanilla and warmth.  The close fades quickly to a subtle but not overpowering sweetness.
M - This is the most surprising aspect.  A beer this big and full should be heavy, and it would not be a knock.  But this is surprisingly drinkable and pleasant.  There is not much spicy warmth, and not a lot of heat from the alcohol, either.  Exceptional.
O - Overall, I am not a huge fan of peppers in my beer, but this one is not brutal.  The flavor is very deep, but it is the feel in the mouth that really separates this brew from other big ABV stouts.  I cannot say I'd seek this out again, but it is not because this beer is anything other than top notch. 1,244 charactersTsar_Riga, Jan 30, 2016
