4.5/5  rDev +0.2%Batch 2 unwaxed
The beer pours an inky black color that leave tan oily looking residue in the glass and is topped by a razor thin, tan head, which settles  quickly around the perimeter. The nose is sweet coffee, spices, and bread upfront, but is cut by slightly burnt caramel and ethanol. It has a coffee forward flavor profile with most of the barrel, chili, and alcohol sitting on the palate in aftertaste. This is a heavy bodied beer, but not syrupy, with adequate carbonation and bright coffee/chili acidity that penetrates the saturating stout base. It's velvety sweet, but neither cocoa nor vanilla seem to dominate (though cocoa lingers a bit longer) and has minimal ethanol. This is definitely a great beer - I'd recommend it to others and will continue to grab when it hits shelves. 791 charactersThePorterSorter, Nov 10, 2013
